As a consequence, most of the PV parameters (e.g., FF, Voc and Jsc) have similar trends in temperature dependency on different substrates, mostly, a negative trend. In accordance with Eqs. (3)–(5), we can conclude that PCE decreases with increasing temperature as temperature has a positive impact on the intrinsic carrier concentration (ni). Jo increases with increasing ni which further decreases the Voc. The steady loss of Jsc on SLG substrate or slight increase on PI substrate, in which the Jsc is not enough to compensate for the loss of Voc, eventually lead to decreased FF and PCE with increasing temperature. Jo, saturation current density, is proportional to the square of the intrinsic carrier concentration for a solar cell which has been modeled [39] as in Eq. (3).3Jo=q×B×DnLnNA+DpLpNDni2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
